Firewall
▪ Firewall is a security mechanism that 
can protect the premises network from 
Internet-based attacks and to provide a 
single choke point where security and 
auditing can be imposed. 
▪ Firewalls are also deployed internal to 
the enterprise network to segregate 
portions of the network.
▪ The firewall provides an additional 
layer of defense, insulating internal 
systems from external networks or 
other parts of the internal network. 
▪ This follows the classic military 
doctrine of “defense in depth,” which is 
just as applicable to IT security.
