Intrusion Detection System (IDS)
Approaches to Intrusion Detection
Misuse detection is based on rules that specify 
system events, sequences of events, or observable 
properties of a system that are believed to be 
indication of security incidents. 
Misuse detectors use various pattern-matching 
algorithms, operating on large databases of attack 
patterns, or signatures. 
▪ An advantage of misuse detection is that it is 
accurate and generates few false alarms. 
▪ A disadvantage is that it cannot detect novel or 
unknown attacks.
