Intrusion Detection System (IDS)
Approaches to Intrusion Detection
Anomaly detection searches for activity that is 
different from the normal behavior of system 
entities and system resources. 
▪ An advantage of anomaly detection is that it is 
able to detect previously unknown attacks 
based on an audit of activity. 
▪ A disadvantage is that there is a significant 
trade-off between false positives and false 
negatives.
