Intrusion Detection System (IDS)
Network
Based 
Intrusion 
Detection System (NIDS)
▪ Network-based ID involves looking at the packets on the 
network as they pass by some sensor. 
▪ Packets are considered to be of interest if they match a 
signature.
▪ Three primary types of signatures are string signatures, port 
signatures, and header condition signatures.
▪ String signatures look for a text string that indicates a possible 
attack.
▪ Port signatures simply watch for connection attempts to well 
known, frequently attacked ports.
▪ Header signatures watch for dangerous or illogical 
combinations in packet headers.
