An NIDS sensor can only see the packets 
that happen to be carried on the network 
segment to which it is attached. 
Accordingly, NIDS deployment is typically 
set up as a number of sensors distributed on 
key network points to gather traffic data and 
feed information on potential threats to a 
central NIDS manager.
